---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — Crestmore Research"
  description="How Crestmore Research uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on its website."
  canonicalUrl="https://crestmoreresearch.com/cookies"
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-page__header">
        <p class="legal-page__label">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="legal-page__title">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-page__meta">Last updated: 1 January 2025</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-page__body">

        <p class="legal-page__intro">
          This Cookie Policy explains how Crestmore Research LLC ("Crestmore", "we", "our") uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on <strong>crestmoreresearch.com</strong>. It should be read in conjunction with our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites function more efficiently, to remember your preferences, and to provide information to website owners about how their site is used. Cookies may be "session" cookies (deleted when you close your browser) or "persistent" cookies (which remain on your device for a set period or until you delete them).</p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use the following categories of cookies on our website:</p>

        <h3>Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
        <p>These cookies are essential for our website to function correctly. They enable core functionality such as security, session management, and accessibility. Because they are strictly necessary, they cannot be disabled.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Session management:</strong> Maintains your session state as you navigate between pages</li>
          <li><strong>Security:</strong> Helps protect against cross-site request forgery and other threats</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics Cookies (with consent)</h3>
        <p>With your consent, we use analytics cookies to understand how visitors interact with our website — which pages are most visited, how long users stay, and where they navigate from. This data is aggregated and anonymised and helps us improve the site.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Analytics provider:</strong> We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool. IP addresses are anonymised and data is not shared with advertising networks.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Preference Cookies (with consent)</h3>
        <p>These cookies remember choices you have made, such as your cookie consent preference, so we do not need to ask you again on future visits.</p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>Our website does not currently load third-party advertising or social media tracking scripts by default. If you follow links to third-party platforms (such as LinkedIn), those platforms may set their own cookies in accordance with their own policies.</p>

        <h2>4. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
        <p>You can manage or withdraw your consent to non-essential cookies at any time by:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies via your browser settings. Note that blocking strictly necessary cookies may affect site functionality.</li>
          <li><strong>Our consent banner:</strong> If our website displays a cookie consent notice, you can update your preferences by clicking the "Cookie Settings" link in our website footer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Useful resources for managing cookies by browser:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Chrome: Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies</li>
          <li>Firefox: Preferences → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li>Safari: Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
          <li>Edge: Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Do Not Track</h2>
        <p>Some browsers transmit a "Do Not Track" (DNT) signal. We endeavour to respect DNT signals where technically feasible. When DNT is detected, we limit cookie use to strictly necessary cookies only.</p>

        <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Cookie Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. We encourage you to review this policy when you visit our site.</p>

        <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For questions about our use of cookies, please contact:</p>
        <address>
          <strong>Crestmore Research LLC — Privacy Office</strong><br />
          245 Park Avenue, Suite 3900<br />
          New York, NY 10167<br />
          <a href="mailto:privacy@crestmoreresearch.com">privacy@crestmoreresearch.com</a>
        </address>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 80px 0 100px;
    background: var(--bg-light);
    min-height: 70vh;
  }

  .legal-page__header {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto 48px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .legal-page__label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-page__title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .legal-page__meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-page__body {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 48px 56px;
  }

  .legal-page__intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .legal-page__body h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin: 40px 0 12px;
  }

  .legal-page__body h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-page__body h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin: 24px 0 8px;
  }

  .legal-page__body p,
  .legal-page__body li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-page__body ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .legal-page__body li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .legal-page__body a {
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .legal-page__body a:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold);
  }

  .legal-page__body address {
    font-style: normal;
    background: var(--bg-light);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-page__body {
      padding: 32px 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
